 Butterworth - Butterworth police are investigating a murder case that occurred over the weekend and have appealed for assistance with leads and information on the deceased. "It is alleged that on Saturday, at about 06:30, a community member found a murdered person at Ngxalathi Village, Butterworth," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "Butterworth police were alerted and when they were at the scene, they discovered that the deceased had suffered bullet injuries on his lower body." He added that the deceased is an unknown man. "No one has been arrested yet," said Capt Manatha. "Butterworth Police are appealing to anyone who has information about the murder and who can identify the deceased to contact them at 047 401 1124." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 